      • getArguments

        private static String getArguments​(Executable method,
                                   boolean typed)
        Returns the argument list of the given method. Method supports 2 modes
        • typed mode : arguments are following their types
        • untyped mode : arguments are printed without any types
        Parameters:
        method - Executable that can be either Method or Constructor - method to generate arguments list of
        typed - indicates whether a mode should be typed or not
        Returns:
        String containing text of arguments list of the given method that consists of
        • list of method's argument names separated by ", " for untyped mode
        • list of method's argument types fully-qualified names followed by method's argument names separated by ", " for untyped mode

      • getMethodImpl

        private static String getMethodImpl​(Executable method,
                                    String newClassName)
        Generates default implementation source code of the given method assuming that it is a method or a constructor of a class with name = newClassName. Implementation is generated to be correct implementation of the given method and formatted using Oracle's java code style
        Parameters:
        method - method or constructor to generate implementation of
        newClassName - name of class containing the given method
        Returns:
        method's default implementation. If the given method is a method then the body of it consists of a single return-statement. Return value is the default value of method's return type. If method's return type is void then return statement has no return value If the given method is a constructor then the body of it consists of a single super constructor invocation statement. Current method's arguments are delegated to super

      • main

        public static void main​(String[] args)
        Provides command line interface for ru.ifmo.rain.sokolov.implementor.Implementor class. Available methods: implement(Class, Path) and implementJar(Class, Path)

        Parameters:
        args - :
        • (1) class name, output path
        • (2) "-jar", class name, output path

        Whether if Class for given class name cannot be loaded or if given an incorrect args array or if invoked method (implement or implementJar) fails then prints corresponding output messages

        When given arguments(1) invokes implement(Class, Path) When given arguments(2) invokes implementJar(Class, Path)

      • implement

        public void implement​(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
        Generates correct implementation source code of given token and produces coresponding .java file to given root Produced implementation consists of single class with name token's name + "Impl" suffix. Impl-class has all default single-statement implementations of all required methods and constructors to be implemented.
        Specified by:
        implement in interface info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.Impler
        Parameters:
        token - Class to be implemented
        root - path to directory for output
        Throws:
        info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - in the following situations:
        • token is null or root is null
        • token represents either a primitive type, final class, enum or array (i.e. token) cannot be implemented
        • root is incorrect path
        • Error occurs while either creating of output file (with corresponding directories) or writing anything to output file
        See Also:
        getMethodImpl(Executable, String)
